1
00:00:08,967 --> 00:00:10,433
<i> You only used me</i>

2
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:13,200
<i>so you could enter this family.</i>

3
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:16,900
<i>But from the very beginning,
Paolo was really your target.</i>

4
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:18,067
<i> I did this for you,</i>

5
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,433
<i>so our plans would not
fall apart.</i>

6
00:00:20,567 --> 00:00:21,833
<i> Is there a problem?</i>

7
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:25,400
<i>Every move, even the slightest
change in expression,</i>

8
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:28,033
<i>I could not help
but read into it.</i>

9
00:00:28,167 --> 00:00:30,400
<i>You knew, but you did not
tell me.</i>

10
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:32,267
<i> You hated me so much</i>

11
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:36,000
<i>that you let my own sibling
and spouse</i>

12
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:37,633
<i> humiliate me like this.</i>

13
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:38,367
<i> Fight back!</i>

14
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,767
<i> Ashley was all I had left,</i>

15
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,900
<i>and then I find out she was
never even mine</i>

16
00:00:42,033 --> 00:00:42,967
<i> in the first place!</i>

17
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:45,033
<i>From now on, I have no sibling!</i>

18
00:00:45,167 --> 00:00:46,900
<i> Edward!</i>

19
00:01:33,633 --> 00:01:36,067
<i> Are you sure about Thea?</i>

20
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,400
<i>How well do you really know her?</i>

21
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:40,400
<i> Edward, get to know her well</i>

22
00:01:40,567 --> 00:01:43,133
<i>if you truly want to be serious
about this relationship.</i>

23
00:01:43,267 --> 00:01:44,567
<i>I just do not want you
to get hurt.</i>

24
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:49,100
<i>If I could turn back time,
I would not have done that.</i>

25
00:01:49,233 --> 00:01:51,300
[GASPS]

26
00:01:51,433 --> 00:01:52,800
Edward, please.

27
00:01:52,933 --> 00:01:56,133
From the very beginning,
you were already deceiving me!

28
00:01:56,267 --> 00:01:58,667
<i>Marj said you can act your way
out of anything.</i>

29
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,467
<i>A business trip with Paolo
for three days?</i>

30
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:01,633
<i> Hon, this is work.</i>

31
00:02:01,767 --> 00:02:02,367
<i> Why you?</i>

32
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:03,967
<i> Because I earned it.</i>

33
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:05,033
<i> Déjà vu.</i>

34
00:02:05,167 --> 00:02:07,633
Everything you do,
everything you say,

35
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:09,667
everything you show me...

36
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,400
<i> Why could I not reach you?</i>

37
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:13,733
<i> You just do not trust me.</i>

38
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,567
All of it was a lie.

39
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:23,700
You only used me so you
could enter this family.

40
00:02:23,833 --> 00:02:24,900
Am I right?

41
00:02:25,033 --> 00:02:26,667
[INTENSE]

42
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,600
You pretended to be on my side,

43
00:02:28,733 --> 00:02:32,767
but from the start,
Paolo was your real target.

44
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:34,200
<i>We already have
so many problems.</i>

45
00:02:34,333 --> 00:02:35,933
<i> Do not add to them.</i>

46
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:40,233
<i> What are you arguing about?</i>

47
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,400
Why, Thea?

48
00:02:48,533 --> 00:02:50,267
What?

49
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,000
Why?

50
00:02:52,133 --> 00:02:53,567
Edward, enough!

51
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:54,667
Why, Thea?

52
00:02:56,833 --> 00:02:59,433
Why did you have to lie to me?

53
00:02:59,567 --> 00:03:01,800
<i>I am pregnant,
and he is the father.</i>

54
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:05,233
<i> That's right.</i>

55
00:03:05,367 --> 00:03:06,367
<i> I am going to be a dad.</i>

56
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:11,800
[WHOOPING AND APPLAUDING]

57
00:03:11,933 --> 00:03:14,067
Why did you have to say Ashley
was my child?

58
00:03:16,933 --> 00:03:20,667
Because that was the deal
between your father and Paolo!

59
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:24,833
[INTENSE]

60
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,767
They know?

61
00:03:26,900 --> 00:03:28,767
Unbelievable...

62
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:30,667
They know?

63
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:31,900
<i> And in return,</i>

64
00:03:32,033 --> 00:03:35,800
<i>you must promise you will never
bother Paolo again.</i>

65
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:36,900
Thea!

66
00:03:38,733 --> 00:03:40,433
You made a fool out of me!

67
00:03:40,567 --> 00:03:43,100
You all made a fool out of me!

68
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:45,733
Edward, believe me!

69
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:47,533
I was going to tell you!

70
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:52,633
But dad wanted me
to stand by the claim

71
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:54,067
that Ash was your child.

72
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:59,400
So the Torrecampo reputation
would not be stained.

73
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:05,133
In exchange,
he funded your startup.

74
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:09,467
[INTENSE]

75
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:11,800
Edward, believe me.

76
00:04:13,667 --> 00:04:15,667
I did this for you.

77
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:18,867
I did this for you.

78
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,933
I agreed so you
would not leave me.

79
00:04:23,067 --> 00:04:25,700
So our plans would
not fall apart.

80
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:26,733
[EXCLAIMS]

81
00:04:26,867 --> 00:04:28,433
- Enough!
- So what?

82
00:04:30,167 --> 00:04:33,833
I am supposed to be grateful
for how you deceived me?

83
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:39,600
Do I need to thank you
for manipulating me?

84
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:45,767
No, Thea!

85
00:04:48,367 --> 00:04:50,200
You did not do this for me!

86
00:04:51,867 --> 00:04:52,967
Edward, please!

87
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:55,433
You did it for yourself!

88
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:56,900
Because you are selfish!

89
00:04:58,067 --> 00:05:00,133
You only think about
your ambition and yourself!

90
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:02,567
Edward, no.

91
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:03,833
Have mercy on me.

92
00:05:03,967 --> 00:05:05,000
We are done.

93
00:05:05,133 --> 00:05:06,767
We are done!

94
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:08,000
No!

95
00:05:08,133 --> 00:05:09,300
Edward, please!

96
00:05:09,433 --> 00:05:10,333
Do not leave me.

97
00:05:10,467 --> 00:05:12,033
Please!
[SOBBING]

98
00:05:12,167 --> 00:05:14,767
I love you so much, Edward,
please!

99
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:17,300
Please! Please!

100
00:05:17,433 --> 00:05:20,367
[SOBBING]

101
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:21,467
What love?

102
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,333
You are not begging
because you love me.

103
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:29,100
You just do not want me
to leave

104
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:30,800
because Paolo did not choose you

105
00:05:30,933 --> 00:05:32,267
even though you have a child
together!

106
00:05:34,267 --> 00:05:35,700
And even now,

107
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:38,867
after your depravity
was exposed,

108
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,867
he still chose Marj.

109
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:45,033
He is still chasing Marj!

110
00:05:45,167 --> 00:05:46,000
And you?

111
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:49,667
Who is chasing you?

112
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:52,000
[WHIMPERS]

113
00:05:56,833 --> 00:06:03,600
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

114
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:05,433
[SOBBING]

115
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:07,667
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

116
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:24,733
Jasmine...

117
00:06:24,867 --> 00:06:27,100
Your body is no longer
responding well

118
00:06:27,233 --> 00:06:28,167
to the treatment.

119
00:06:29,467 --> 00:06:31,067
So, we need to change the plan.

120
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:37,267
The doctor said the next best
step is a stem cell transplant.

121
00:06:38,967 --> 00:06:41,000
This treatment will be
difficult again,

122
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:43,533
just like the last one, Jasmine.

123
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:46,733
But it does cure patients
like you.

124
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:50,833
Stem cell transplant?

125
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,967
Like a bone marrow transplant?

126
00:06:57,200 --> 00:07:00,733
I have been reading
about it a lot.

127
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:05,933
They say it is more painful
than the treatments I have had.

128
00:07:08,767 --> 00:07:14,300
And the only reason patients get
it is because they are dying.

129
00:07:14,467 --> 00:07:15,533
[SIGHS]

130
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:18,400
My child,

131
00:07:20,533 --> 00:07:22,467
I will not let that happen,
okay?

132
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:26,000
This transplant
is our only hope.

133
00:07:27,667 --> 00:07:31,767
We are doing everything possible
to make sure you live

134
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:33,333
and get better, okay?

135
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:40,000
Mom, Dad, I am really scared.

136
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,600
I know you are scared.

137
00:07:44,867 --> 00:07:46,667
Your father and I
are scared too.

138
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:51,000
[PHONE BUZZING]

139
00:07:52,733 --> 00:07:54,533
[LINE RINGING]

140
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:56,833
Paolo, please answer my call.

141
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:02,833
My child, it is normal
to be afraid.

142
00:08:03,667 --> 00:08:07,800
What matters is that
we face this bravely.

143
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:12,467
Do not worry, because we
are always here by your side.

144
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:15,600
And we will fight with you.

145
00:08:15,733 --> 00:08:20,267
[PHONE BUZZING]

146
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,167
[BUSY TONE]

147
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:22,400
[SCOFFS]

148
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:28,400
Your mom and I already had blood
tests to see

149
00:08:28,533 --> 00:08:36,100
if either of us is a good match

150
00:08:36,233 --> 00:08:40,367
to be your bone marrow donor,
okay?

151
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:47,100
The doctor said there is a good
chance one of us will be.

152
00:08:48,567 --> 00:08:50,700
That is why we are full of hope,
my child.

153
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:54,033
[INTENSE]

154
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:59,600
[PHONE KEYS CLICKING]

155
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:05,467
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

156
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:15,533
[NOTIFICATION CHIMES]

157
00:09:15,667 --> 00:09:16,667
Stop crying now.

158
00:09:19,133 --> 00:09:21,567
<i>Edward already knows
about Ashley.</i>

159
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:22,633
<i> I had to tell him the truth,</i>

160
00:09:22,767 --> 00:09:24,733
<i>or he would take her away
from me.</i>

161
00:09:24,867 --> 00:09:26,233
<i> What are we going to do?</i>

162
00:09:26,367 --> 00:09:29,667
[INTENSE]

163
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:32,167
Is there a problem?

164
00:09:36,733 --> 00:09:38,667
Why are you suddenly sweating?

165
00:09:40,133 --> 00:09:40,800
What is wrong?

166
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:42,767
What? Who texted you?

167
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:43,867
Oh, it is just a client.

168
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:44,800
They are having second thoughts

169
00:09:44,933 --> 00:09:47,467
about selling their ancestral
house.

170
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:52,733
Dad will be furious again
if I lose this property.

171
00:09:56,100 --> 00:10:00,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

172
00:10:00,533 --> 00:10:02,900
Do not cry now, okay?

173
00:10:03,067 --> 00:10:12,867
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

174
00:10:16,933 --> 00:10:19,833
Mom, I already spoke
with Hannah.

175
00:10:19,967 --> 00:10:22,333
You can stay at the apartment
for now, okay?

176
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:25,633
Things are still too chaotic
at the Torrecampo house.

177
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:28,467
It is fine, Marj.

178
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,933
After all that had happened...

179
00:10:31,067 --> 00:10:37,333
I do not want to force myself
in there anyway.

180
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,100
[SIGHS]

181
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,067
What's the problem, Marj?

182
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:51,167
Because it feels like something
else is bothering you, Marj.

183
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:52,300
What is it?

184
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:59,467
I saw Paolo talking to someone
on his phone...

185
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:03,100
He said it was a client,
but he seemed worried.

186
00:11:03,233 --> 00:11:06,533
He told me he is afraid
of suddenly losing the client.

187
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:09,267
But I am doubtful.

188
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:12,400
I do not know anymore.

189
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:17,467
But, Marj, did you not say
you would get tested

190
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:21,533
to know who matches
as Jasmine's donor?

191
00:11:22,700 --> 00:11:26,533
Maybe he is just worried
about what the results will be.

192
00:11:28,033 --> 00:11:29,200
I do not know anymore, Mom.

193
00:11:30,533 --> 00:11:31,700
After what happened,

194
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,867
I cannot stop myself
from putting malice

195
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,333
into everything he does.

196
00:11:37,367 --> 00:11:42,367
Every movement, every word,

197
00:11:42,533 --> 00:11:45,367
even the slightest change
in expression,

198
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:47,733
I give meaning to it.

199
00:11:49,867 --> 00:11:50,633
[SIGHS]

200
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,233
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

201
00:11:54,367 --> 00:11:55,333
Marj...

202
00:11:58,133 --> 00:12:02,867
You know, my child,
that is how it really is.

203
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:07,133
You no longer trust
anything he does.

204
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:14,067
That seems normal for anyone
who has been betrayed.

205
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:17,300
I hope my suspicion is wrong.

206
00:12:17,467 --> 00:12:19,200
After everything that happened,

207
00:12:20,767 --> 00:12:23,633
I hope my spouse is hiding
nothing from me anymore.

208
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,200
Marj.

209
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:35,000
My men are saying it is still
not safe to enter my house,

210
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:36,867
even briefly.

211
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:40,500
I instructed them
to retrieve items

212
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:42,933
that were not affected
by the fire.

213
00:12:43,067 --> 00:12:46,567
<i>We are first ensuring
that no asbestos spread</i>

214
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:48,433
<i>due to the age of the house,
Sir.</i>

215
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,733
Okay, just update me...

216
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:54,133
when it is cleared.

217
00:12:56,467 --> 00:12:57,433
Thank you.

218
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:00,133
Where is Paolo?

219
00:13:04,033 --> 00:13:05,433
Who let you in?

220
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,333
I already made it clear

221
00:13:12,467 --> 00:13:14,067
that you are no longer welcome
in this house.

222
00:13:15,133 --> 00:13:18,033
You have the nerve to rub my
mistakes in my face.

223
00:13:18,933 --> 00:13:21,233
Yet you and Paolo
both owe me greatly.

224
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:24,300
I do not know
what you are talking about.

225
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,267
I know.

226
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:31,100
I know I am such a failure
to you.

227
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:32,967
I am such a disappointment!

228
00:13:36,367 --> 00:13:39,200
You could not even love me
as your child!

229
00:13:39,333 --> 00:13:41,100
Every day we see each other,

230
00:13:41,233 --> 00:13:44,867
you never fail to remind me
that I am a failure!

231
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:48,700
But that does not give you
the right to toy with my life.

232
00:13:51,233 --> 00:13:52,700
You knew about Ashley, right?

233
00:13:53,733 --> 00:13:54,900
You and Paolo?

234
00:14:00,433 --> 00:14:01,100
Sit down and listen.

235
00:14:01,233 --> 00:14:02,267
No, you listen to me!

236
00:14:05,067 --> 00:14:07,167
You knew, but you did not
tell me.

237
00:14:08,367 --> 00:14:11,500
Instead, you tolerated
the two of them deceiving me!

238
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:15,667
Dad...

239
00:14:17,467 --> 00:14:18,767
I know you never liked me.

240
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:23,367
But I never thought
you hated me enough

241
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:28,233
to let my own sibling and spouse
humiliate me like this!

242
00:14:29,233 --> 00:14:30,167
What kind of father are you?

243
00:14:30,300 --> 00:14:32,567
You should be thanking me

244
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:34,433
for giving you
the life you wanted!

245
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:38,467
Because of me,
you got your trophy spouse.

246
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,767
Your funding,
your precious child,

247
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:44,833
without any effort.

248
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:46,867
That is always the case
with you, Dad!

249
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,900
Is it not?

250
00:14:49,033 --> 00:14:52,633
You just want everyone
to owe you.

251
00:14:53,767 --> 00:14:54,933
Even your own child?

252
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:59,133
Paolo is not the only one
who needed you.

253
00:15:02,667 --> 00:15:03,967
I needed you, Dad.

254
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:06,133
I needed you!

255
00:15:06,267 --> 00:15:09,567
I needed a father
who would protect me.

256
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:12,133
But instead, you kept
your golden child

257
00:15:12,267 --> 00:15:15,033
shiny, beautiful, and perfect

258
00:15:15,167 --> 00:15:18,700
in front of others,
at my expense!

259
00:15:18,833 --> 00:15:20,467
You know what,

260
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,767
you are a completely
worthless father!

261
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,733
[THUDS]

262
00:15:26,867 --> 00:15:28,600
[INTENSE]

263
00:15:28,733 --> 00:15:31,433
That is still not enough
for everything you did to me!

264
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:35,800
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

265
00:15:38,633 --> 00:15:39,400
[DOOR SLAMS]

266
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:53,900
It says here
in what I am reading...

267
00:15:54,033 --> 00:15:56,133
Hi, Jas.

268
00:15:56,267 --> 00:15:57,800
What are you doing here?

269
00:15:59,967 --> 00:16:01,033
What do you mean?

270
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:05,167
I always visit whenever
you are here, right?

271
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:10,733
Are you still angry at me
because of our parents' issues?

272
00:16:13,267 --> 00:16:18,167
But we promised each other
we would stay solid

273
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:19,733
no matter what happens, right?

274
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:26,433
Sure, but that was before
I saw you hugging Xander.

275
00:16:31,367 --> 00:16:32,767
I can explain, Jas.

276
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:34,333
You knew I liked him, Ash.

277
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:38,767
I told you to take care of him
while I was recovering,

278
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:40,433
not steal him from me.

279
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:42,533
I swear, Jas,
it is not like that.

280
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:43,800
Then what is it?

281
00:16:47,167 --> 00:16:52,167
When your illness got worse,
when our family fell apart,

282
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:56,333
when there were times
I felt my world was collapsing,

283
00:16:56,467 --> 00:16:57,767
Xander was there.

284
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:02,967
He has been a great friend
to me, Jas.

285
00:17:04,633 --> 00:17:05,600
Just leave.

286
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,400
I know you will get angry
at me just because...

287
00:17:13,467 --> 00:17:22,600
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:17:22,767 --> 00:17:24,400
You know what
is more heartbreaking?

289
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:30,233
It is the fact
that when I was falling apart,

290
00:17:30,367 --> 00:17:31,600
you had Xander.

291
00:17:33,067 --> 00:17:34,900
I had no one.

292
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:36,033
That is not true, Jas.

293
00:17:36,167 --> 00:17:37,833
It is!

294
00:17:37,967 --> 00:17:39,367
You are using my illness

295
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:41,967
and our family's mess
to gain sympathy

296
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:45,067
and take Xander from me.

297
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,267
Because you liked him all along.

298
00:17:48,667 --> 00:17:50,267
You are just like your mother.

299
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:59,133
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

300
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:16,867
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

301
00:18:23,033 --> 00:18:24,367
I am sorry.

302
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:27,900
[DRAMATIC]

303
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:32,067
[SOBBING]

304
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:34,300
[MARJ SIGHS]

305
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:36,633
I am sorry.

306
00:18:36,767 --> 00:18:41,800
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

307
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:53,467
[ASHLEY SOBBING]

308
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:54,600
Ashley.

309
00:18:56,467 --> 00:18:57,733
Aunt Marj.

310
00:18:57,867 --> 00:18:58,867
It is okay.

311
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:01,167
Here.

312
00:19:02,867 --> 00:19:06,367
I will be the one to apologize
for what Jasmine did.

313
00:19:07,067 --> 00:19:09,567
I know she did not mean
to say that to you.

314
00:19:11,833 --> 00:19:16,033
I am not justifying
what Jasmine did,

315
00:19:16,167 --> 00:19:19,033
but I know she is just scared
right now.

316
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:25,200
That is why she feels
like she is losing hope.

317
00:19:25,333 --> 00:19:26,300
No matter what she does,

318
00:19:26,433 --> 00:19:27,733
it feels like it will not
matter.

319
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:36,367
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:49,233
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

321
00:19:49,367 --> 00:19:50,567
[FOUL WORDS]

322
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:52,600
So, you have been messing
with me for years.

323
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:53,500
[PAOLO GRUNTS]

324
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:55,533
[THUDS]

325
00:19:55,667 --> 00:19:56,333
[GRUNTS]

326
00:19:57,233 --> 00:19:58,900
[THUDDING]

327
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:00,700
[GRUNTING]

328
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:02,700
Sir Edward, stop it!

329
00:20:02,867 --> 00:20:03,867
- Is it not enough...
- Stop meddling!

330
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,467
that you betrayed me?

331
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,267
Do you really have to toy
with me too?

332
00:20:08,433 --> 00:20:09,600
Fight back!

333
00:20:09,733 --> 00:20:11,733
Is that not what you want,
always winning?

334
00:20:11,867 --> 00:20:12,833
[THUDS]

335
00:20:12,967 --> 00:20:13,733
Fight back!

336
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:15,133
[THUDDING]

337
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:17,567
[GRUNTING]

338
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:18,533
[GRUNTS]

339
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:23,533
[INTENSE]

340
00:20:26,033 --> 00:20:28,033
I understand, Auntie.

341
00:20:30,267 --> 00:20:32,900
It is just that...

342
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:34,967
she is not wrong.

343
00:20:36,967 --> 00:20:41,433
I was selfish for letting
myself get close to Xander,

344
00:20:41,567 --> 00:20:43,633
even though I knew that
she would hurt her.

345
00:20:45,267 --> 00:20:47,600
This is all my fault, Auntie.

346
00:20:47,733 --> 00:20:49,500
I deserve to be told...

347
00:20:51,233 --> 00:20:52,200
Ashley, no.

348
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:55,167
Do not say that.

349
00:20:56,367 --> 00:20:57,567
It is my fault.

350
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:01,500
I worried so much about Jasmine

351
00:21:01,633 --> 00:21:04,800
that I forgot to be a mother
in other ways.

352
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:12,833
To remind her that no matter how
serious her condition becomes,

353
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,767
she should not let her heart
be consumed by anger.

354
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,867
All these years,
you have been mocking me!

355
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,300
I am sure of that.

356
00:21:20,433 --> 00:21:22,200
[GRUNTS]

357
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:24,367
Because I am the fool

358
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:27,900
who happily took
on your responsibilities!

359
00:21:28,033 --> 00:21:30,233
Without knowing anything!

360
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:31,200
[GRUNTS]

361
00:21:34,300 --> 00:21:35,633
Ashley is all I have left.

362
00:21:37,133 --> 00:21:38,967
Ashley is the only one
on my side.

363
00:21:40,733 --> 00:21:44,667
She is the only person
who does not look down on me.

364
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:48,700
And then I find out

365
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:51,300
she was never even mine
in the first place!

366
00:21:51,433 --> 00:21:53,400
[THUDS]

367
00:21:53,533 --> 00:21:58,300
Even after what mom did to you,
you are still kind to me.

368
00:21:59,900 --> 00:22:01,900
You are not your mother.

369
00:22:02,033 --> 00:22:03,333
You are Ashley.

370
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:06,133
Jasmine's best friend.

371
00:22:07,033 --> 00:22:09,000
Her cousin.

372
00:22:09,133 --> 00:22:11,000
We love you very much.

373
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,800
I love you very much too.

374
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:22,667
And I see Jasmine
as my sister now.

375
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:28,433
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

376
00:22:28,567 --> 00:22:32,533
Dear, may I ask something
from you?

377
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:36,100
Do not give up on Jasmine, okay?

378
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:40,800
She is just scared right now,
but she really needs you.

379
00:22:41,900 --> 00:22:46,867
I promise I will not
let her down anymore.

380
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:51,000
I will never hurt her again.

381
00:22:59,900 --> 00:23:02,233
[SOBBING]

382
00:23:02,367 --> 00:23:04,000
[THUDS]

383
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:04,667
[EXCLAIMS]

384
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,767
I am sorry, Edward.

385
00:23:06,900 --> 00:23:07,500
Sorry, Edward.

386
00:23:07,633 --> 00:23:09,067
I am sorry.

387
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:09,600
[THUDS]

388
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:11,000
[GRUNTS]

389
00:23:11,133 --> 00:23:11,833
[GRUNTING]

390
00:23:11,967 --> 00:23:13,000
<i> You are a liar!</i>

391
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,433
If you really wanted
to say that,

392
00:23:16,567 --> 00:23:17,633
you should have done it
long ago.

393
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:20,767
You are so arrogant!

394
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:26,000
Because you want to prove
you can take anything

395
00:23:26,133 --> 00:23:28,000
or anyone from me,
just like you always have!

396
00:23:29,567 --> 00:23:34,000
But instead, you chose to make a
fool out of me like a sick joke!

397
00:23:34,133 --> 00:23:34,967
[THUDS]

398
00:23:37,533 --> 00:23:40,300
[GRUNTS]

399
00:23:40,433 --> 00:23:41,700
I was weak!

400
00:23:41,833 --> 00:23:42,900
[THUDS]

401
00:23:43,033 --> 00:23:45,200
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

402
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:48,967
[PAOLO GRUNTS]

403
00:23:51,433 --> 00:23:53,100
I thought...

404
00:23:53,233 --> 00:23:55,700
I admit, I was weak.

405
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:02,700
I thought everything would
be easier if I walked away.

406
00:24:04,967 --> 00:24:09,767
By pretending nothing
ever happened.

407
00:24:09,900 --> 00:24:14,200
But I regret that
that was my decision.

408
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:20,567
My conscience never
leaves me alone.

409
00:24:21,833 --> 00:24:27,667
Because it always reminds me
how I ruined your life, Edward.

410
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,100
Is that so?

411
00:24:29,267 --> 00:24:31,900
Is that so? Is that why you were
caught with my wife

412
00:24:32,033 --> 00:24:32,933
a few weeks ago?

413
00:24:33,067 --> 00:24:34,433
I am sorry!

414
00:24:36,333 --> 00:24:37,000
Shut up!

415
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:41,867
No one can ever forgive someone
like you!

416
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:44,700
Fight back!

417
00:24:44,833 --> 00:24:46,367
Fight back! Get up!

418
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:48,267
Fight back!

419
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:49,233
[THUDS]

420
00:24:51,633 --> 00:24:52,867
[THUDS]

421
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,900
Fight back!

422
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:57,900
[INTENSE]

423
00:24:58,033 --> 00:24:59,500
[THUDS]

424
00:24:59,633 --> 00:25:00,067
[GRUNTS]

425
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:00,800
Shut up!

426
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:02,600
[THUDS]

427
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:04,100
[GRUNTS]

428
00:25:04,233 --> 00:25:05,433
Edward, stop it!

429
00:25:05,567 --> 00:25:06,767
Please, stop!

430
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:07,933
Please, stop it!

431
00:25:08,067 --> 00:25:09,767
Do not hurt your older brother,
please!

432
00:25:09,900 --> 00:25:11,333
Stop it, Edward!

433
00:25:11,467 --> 00:25:13,300
Please, stop!

434
00:25:13,433 --> 00:25:16,200
From now on,
I no longer have a sibling.

435
00:25:18,167 --> 00:25:19,233
My older brother is dead to me!

436
00:25:22,967 --> 00:25:23,933
Edward!

437
00:25:25,067 --> 00:25:26,067
Edward!

438
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:29,967
[SOBBING]

439
00:25:30,100 --> 00:25:34,467
[INTENSE]

440
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:38,267
[SOBBING]

441
00:25:38,433 --> 00:25:41,533
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

442
00:25:43,433 --> 00:25:44,233
My child, I am sorry.

443
00:25:44,367 --> 00:25:45,933
I am dragging you
into all this chaos.

444
00:25:46,067 --> 00:25:47,333
I hate to do this right now.

445
00:25:47,467 --> 00:25:49,500
I think I need to leave
the house for a while.

446
00:25:49,633 --> 00:25:52,533
Edward, if this is about
what Paolo did to you,

447
00:25:52,667 --> 00:25:54,733
I will apologize for him.

448
00:25:54,867 --> 00:25:58,767
No. Our spouses are the ones
who caused us pain.

449
00:25:58,900 --> 00:26:00,500
You and Jasmine should
leave this place too.

450
00:26:00,633 --> 00:26:02,500
You do not deserve
this kind of family.

451
00:26:02,633 --> 00:26:03,667
Are you joking?

452
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:06,533
Do you want me to take back
your dismissal?

453
00:26:06,667 --> 00:26:08,233
I am not leaving.

454
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,900
Do not force me, Greg.

455
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:13,333
Otherwise, I will expose
all the dirt I know,

456
00:26:13,467 --> 00:26:15,033
especially about you!

457
00:26:16,233 --> 00:26:17,667
Are you threatening me?

458
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:19,733
Yes, Sir Greg.

459
00:26:19,867 --> 00:26:21,100
We are not compatible?

460
00:26:21,233 --> 00:26:22,833
Does that mean we cannot donate?

461
00:26:22,967 --> 00:26:24,600
But what will happen
to my child?

462
00:26:24,733 --> 00:26:25,633
What about her?

463
00:26:25,767 --> 00:26:27,400
I will talk to mom.

464
00:26:27,533 --> 00:26:30,400
I will convince everyone I know.

465
00:26:30,533 --> 00:26:32,933
We will ask them
if they can get tested.

466
00:26:33,067 --> 00:26:35,133
Paolo, we are not asking them.

467
00:26:35,267 --> 00:26:38,300
None of them can refuse to help.

468
00:26:38,433 --> 00:26:40,267
There is still hope, Ma'am Marj.

469
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:41,467
Hello, Ms. Yolly?

470
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:43,033
I would like to talk to you.

471
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:45,333
You need to know the truth.

472
00:26:45,467 --> 00:26:46,500
What truth?
